1
00:00:01,828 --> 00:00:04,288
Who the winny-binny boy?

2
00:00:04,539 --> 00:00:10,128
You the winny-winny-binny-binny boy!

3
00:00:10,336 --> 00:00:12,338
Don't cry.

4
00:00:12,588 --> 00:00:16,175
Don't cry.

5
00:00:16,384 --> 00:00:18,355
Why is he still crying?

6
00:00:19,048 --> 00:00:23,585
Don't worry. There's nothing that
can't be solved by happy keys.

7
00:00:24,325 --> 00:00:28,137
Yeah, I always feel much better when
someone shakes jagged metal in my face.

8
00:00:30,928 --> 00:00:32,972
Let me hold him for a sec.

9
00:00:33,222 --> 00:00:35,683
Here we go.

10
00:00:35,933 --> 00:00:38,310
There we are.

11
00:00:38,644 --> 00:00:39,854
Maybe it's me.

12
00:00:40,304 --> 00:00:44,183
Don't be silly. Ben loves you.
He's just being Mr. Cranky Pants.

13
00:00:44,433 --> 00:00:48,062
You know, I once dated
a Miss Cranky Pants.

14
00:00:48,312 --> 00:00:51,440
Lovely girl. Kind of moody.

15
00:00:51,690 --> 00:00:53,776
There we go, all better.

16
00:00:54,026 --> 00:00:57,571
There's my little boy.

17
00:01:02,493 --> 00:01:06,330
Can I see something?

18
00:01:18,592 --> 00:01:19,468
Cool!

19
00:01:19,718 --> 00:01:22,864
He hates me.
My nephew hates me!

20
00:01:22,899 --> 00:01:24,486
I'm unemployed
and my nephew hates me!

21
00:01:24,521 --> 00:01:27,769
Oh, stop, don't do this.
You're just unemployed.

22
00:01:29,931 --> 00:01:32,600
What if my own baby hates me?
What do I do then?

23
00:01:32,850 --> 00:01:34,394
Monica, stop! This is nuts.

24
00:01:34,644 --> 00:01:39,232
Do you know how long it'll be
before you have to deal with this?

25
00:01:39,482 --> 00:01:43,611
You don't even have a boyfriend yet.

26
00:01:44,445 --> 00:01:47,615
Joey, she does not look fat.

27
00:01:47,866 --> 00:01:50,994
The One With the Baby on the Bus

28
00:02:33,446 --> 00:02:36,365
Here you go.

29
00:02:39,410 --> 00:02:42,788
Goo, goo, goo!

30
00:02:44,498 --> 00:02:48,878
That is so funny!
Let me see that a sec.

31
00:02:55,009 --> 00:02:55,801
You okay?

32
00:02:56,052 --> 00:02:58,846
I don't know.

33
00:02:59,514 --> 00:03:01,015
What's in this pie?

34
00:03:01,265 --> 00:03:04,936
I don't know. Butter and eggs
and flour and lime and kiwi...

35
00:03:05,186 --> 00:03:07,772
Kiwi? Kiwi?!

36
00:03:08,022 --> 00:03:09,482
You said it was a key lime pie.

37
00:03:09,732 --> 00:03:13,653
No, I didn't. I said kiwi lime.
That's what makes it so special.

38
00:03:13,903 --> 00:03:17,406
That's what's gonna kill me.

39
00:03:17,865 --> 00:03:19,450
I'm allergic to kiwi.

40
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:24,914
No, you're not. You're allergic
to lobster and peanuts and...

41
00:03:25,665 --> 00:03:26,874
Oh, my God!

42
00:03:27,124 --> 00:03:29,502
It's definitely getting worse.

43
00:03:29,752 --> 00:03:31,587
Is your tongue swelling up?

44
00:03:31,838 --> 00:03:35,007
Either that or my mouth
is getting smaller!

45
00:03:35,258 --> 00:03:37,426
Get your coat.
We're going to the hospital.

46
00:03:37,677 --> 00:03:39,887
- Will he be okay?
- He's gotta get a shot.

47
00:03:40,137 --> 00:03:43,432
You know, actually,
it's getting better. It is.

48
00:03:43,683 --> 00:03:47,019
Let's not go.
Anyone up for Scrabble?

49
00:03:47,270 --> 00:03:49,230
Jacket, now!

50
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:53,276
What about Ben? We can't
bring a baby to the hospital.

51
00:03:53,526 --> 00:03:55,278
We'll watch him.

52
00:03:55,528 --> 00:03:58,072
I don't think so.

53
00:03:58,322 --> 00:04:02,869
I have seven Catholic sisters.
I've taken care of hundreds of kids.

54
00:04:03,119 --> 00:04:05,037
Come on, we want to do it.
Don't we?

55
00:04:05,288 --> 00:04:07,331
I was gonna play basketball...

56
00:04:07,582 --> 00:04:10,460
...but I guess that's out the window.

57
00:04:10,710 --> 00:04:13,796
If you take him out for a walk,
remember to bring his hat.

58
00:04:14,046 --> 00:04:16,799
There's milk in the refrigerator
and diapers in the bag.

59
00:04:17,049 --> 00:04:18,468
Hat, milk...

60
00:04:18,718 --> 00:04:21,053
Got it!

61
00:04:29,103 --> 00:04:30,730
Consider it done!

62
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:31,814
You understood?

63
00:04:32,064 --> 00:04:36,444
My uncle Sal has a really big tongue.

64
00:04:36,903 --> 00:04:40,615
Is he the one
with the beautiful wife?

65
00:04:45,244 --> 00:04:48,664
You want to hear the song
I'm singing this afternoon?

66
00:04:48,915 --> 00:04:52,919
I wrote it this morning in the shower.

67
00:04:53,753 --> 00:04:58,549
<i>I'm in the shower
And I'm writing a song</i>

68
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:04,013
<i>Stop me if you've heard it</i>

69
00:05:04,847 --> 00:05:08,643
<i>My skin is soapy and my hair is wet</i>

70
00:05:08,893 --> 00:05:14,607
<i>And Tegrin spelled backward is nirget</i>

71
00:05:16,901 --> 00:05:22,532
Rachel, sweetheart,
could I see you for a minute?

72
00:05:24,784 --> 00:05:26,369
What's up?

73
00:05:26,619 --> 00:05:28,329
FYI:

74
00:05:28,579 --> 00:05:32,708
I've decided to pay a professional
musician to play here on Sundays.

75
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:37,088
Her name is Stephanie something.
She's supposed to be very good.

76
00:05:37,338 --> 00:05:40,049
But what about Phoebe?

77
00:05:40,299 --> 00:05:43,719
It's not that your friend is bad.

78
00:05:43,970 --> 00:05:47,557
It's that she's so bad...

79
00:05:47,598 --> 00:05:52,311
...she makes me want to put my finger
through my eye into my brain...

80
00:05:52,562 --> 00:05:55,732
...and swirl it around.

81
00:05:56,315 --> 00:05:59,318
Okay, so you're not a fan.

82
00:05:59,569 --> 00:06:04,031
But, I mean, come on.
You cannot do this to her.

83
00:06:06,492 --> 00:06:07,994
I have to do this to her?

84
00:06:08,244 --> 00:06:10,329
<i>Lather, rinse, repeat</i>

85
00:06:10,580 --> 00:06:12,749
<i>And lather, rinse, repeat</i>

86
00:06:12,999 --> 00:06:16,461
<i>And lather, rinse, repeat</i>

87
00:06:16,711 --> 00:06:19,922
<i>As needed</i>

88
00:06:25,094 --> 00:06:26,721
We didn't bring enough stuff.

89
00:06:26,971 --> 00:06:29,474
Did you forget to pack
the baby's anvil?

90
00:06:29,724 --> 00:06:31,934
I'm telling you, it'll be worth it.

91
00:06:32,185 --> 00:06:34,645
It's a known fact
that women love babies.

92
00:06:34,896 --> 00:06:39,275
Women love guys who love babies.
It's the sensitive thing.

93
00:06:39,525 --> 00:06:43,863
Aim him at that pack of babes.
Maybe one of them will break away.

94
00:06:44,113 --> 00:06:47,367
Wait, forget them.
We got one. Hard left.

95
00:06:47,617 --> 00:06:49,452
- Give me the baby.
- No, I got him.

96
00:06:49,702 --> 00:06:50,828
Come on, seriously.

97
00:06:51,079 --> 00:06:54,499
Oh, seriously, you want him?

98
00:06:57,668 --> 00:06:59,420
Who is this little cutie-pie?

99
00:06:59,670 --> 00:07:02,340
Well, don't think me immodest, but...

100
00:07:02,590 --> 00:07:05,218
...me.

101
00:07:05,468 --> 00:07:06,386
Want to smell him?

102
00:07:06,636 --> 00:07:10,264
I assume we're talking about the baby?

103
00:07:11,432 --> 00:07:16,229
He's got that great baby smell.
Get a whiff of his head.

104
00:07:16,979 --> 00:07:19,816
My uterus just skipped a beat.

105
00:07:20,066 --> 00:07:21,234
What'd I tell you?

106
00:07:21,484 --> 00:07:23,152
It's great you're doing this.

107
00:07:23,403 --> 00:07:25,321
Well, we are great guys.

108
00:07:25,571 --> 00:07:28,700
My brother and his boyfriend
have been trying to adopt.

109
00:07:28,950 --> 00:07:32,870
What agency did you two go through?

110
00:07:35,998 --> 00:07:37,542
But this is my gig.

111
00:07:37,792 --> 00:07:39,210
This is where I play.

112
00:07:39,460 --> 00:07:41,921
My name is written out there in chalk.

113
00:07:42,171 --> 00:07:46,426
You know, you can't just erase chalk.

114
00:07:48,302 --> 00:07:49,512
Honey, I'm sorry.

115
00:07:49,762 --> 00:07:52,015
And he's going to
be paying this woman?

116
00:07:52,265 --> 00:07:55,143
Why doesn't he just give her
a throne and a crown?

117
00:07:55,393 --> 00:08:00,898
And, like, a gold stick
with a ball on top?

118
00:08:01,149 --> 00:08:04,736
Terry is a jerk! That's why
we always say, "Terry's a jerk!"

119
00:08:04,986 --> 00:08:08,948
That's where that came from.

120
00:08:10,199 --> 00:08:13,703
You probably did everything you could.

121
00:08:13,953 --> 00:08:19,375
You know what? Let me just
see what else I could do.

122
00:08:20,752 --> 00:08:23,713
Just let her go on after
Stephanie whatever her name is.

123
00:08:23,963 --> 00:08:26,632
You won't be here.
You don't pay her.

124
00:08:26,883 --> 00:08:28,134
I don't know.

125
00:08:28,384 --> 00:08:30,219
I'll clean the cappuccino machine!

126
00:08:30,470 --> 00:08:34,349
You don't clean
the cappuccino machine?

127
00:08:34,432 --> 00:08:37,268
Of course I clean it.

128
00:08:37,518 --> 00:08:40,188
I mean, I will clean it.

129
00:08:40,438 --> 00:08:41,981
I mean, I will clean it.

130
00:08:42,231 --> 00:08:46,653
All right, fine, fine, fine!

131
00:08:50,156 --> 00:08:51,491
- Done.
- Really?

132
00:08:51,741 --> 00:08:53,743
Who's working for you, babe?

133
00:08:53,993 --> 00:08:58,581
Oh, my God! This is so exciting!
How much am I gonna get?

134
00:08:58,831 --> 00:09:00,333
What?

135
00:09:00,583 --> 00:09:03,711
He's paying the people
who were playing.

136
00:09:03,962 --> 00:09:09,092
I meant, he's paying that other woman
because she's a professional.

137
00:09:09,342 --> 00:09:13,763
I'm not gonna be the only one
who's not getting paid.

138
00:09:13,972 --> 00:09:15,431
I'm sorry, no!

139
00:09:15,682 --> 00:09:19,978
No, I'm not some sloppy second,
you know, charity band.

140
00:09:20,228 --> 00:09:22,730
There are thousands of places
in this city...

141
00:09:22,981 --> 00:09:25,650
...where people would pay
to hear me play.

142
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:27,777
<i>When I play, I play for me</i>

143
00:09:28,027 --> 00:09:30,029
<i>I don't need your charity</i>

144
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:33,199
Thank you!

145
00:09:39,914 --> 00:09:43,167
I'm not getting a shot.
Maybe they can take the needle...

146
00:09:43,418 --> 00:09:47,505
...and squirt it into my mouth.
Like a squirt gun.

147
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,665
Honey, why don't we just wait
and see what the doctor says.

148
00:09:48,869 --> 00:09:51,776
They've got to be able to do something.
I mean, these are the nineties.

149
00:09:52,855 --> 00:09:55,358
Hello there. I'm Dr. Carlin.

150
00:09:55,608 --> 00:09:59,320
I see someone's having
a little allergic reaction.

151
00:09:59,570 --> 00:10:03,533
Doctor, can I see you
for just a moment?

152
00:10:04,117 --> 00:10:07,870
My brother has
a slight phobia about needles.

153
00:10:08,121 --> 00:10:12,500
Did you tell him
about my squirt gun idea?

154
00:10:12,625 --> 00:10:14,961
My brother, the Ph.D.,
would like to know...

155
00:10:15,211 --> 00:10:18,423
...if there's any way
to treat this orally?

156
00:10:18,673 --> 00:10:23,678
Under these circumstances, it has to be
an injection, and it has to be now.

157
00:10:23,928 --> 00:10:26,681
So?

158
00:10:27,765 --> 00:10:31,477
Go and have a seat. The doctor
says it's got to be a needle.

159
00:10:31,728 --> 00:10:37,942
You're just going to have to be brave.
Can you do that for me?

160
00:10:39,527 --> 00:10:44,032
Oh, boy! You are doing so good.

161
00:10:44,282 --> 00:10:46,909
You want to squeeze my hand?

162
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:49,162
Ross, don't squeeze it so hard.

163
00:10:49,412 --> 00:10:51,914
Honey, really.
Don't squeeze it so hard!

164
00:10:52,165 --> 00:10:55,418
Let go of my hand!

165
00:10:57,503 --> 00:10:59,964
Good plan. Next time
we want to pick up women...

166
00:11:00,214 --> 00:11:02,967
...we should go to
the park and make out.

167
00:11:03,217 --> 00:11:06,262
Taxi! Taxi!

168
00:11:06,971 --> 00:11:09,766
Look at that talent.

169
00:11:11,642 --> 00:11:13,686
Just practicing. You're good.

170
00:11:13,936 --> 00:11:15,688
Carry on.

171
00:11:15,938 --> 00:11:17,899
Wait, wait, wait!

172
00:11:18,149 --> 00:11:21,277
Hey, you. He's just adorable.

173
00:11:21,527 --> 00:11:27,283
Can you tell him that?
Because he thinks he looks too pink.

174
00:11:27,325 --> 00:11:32,163
- What are you guys out doing today?
- We're not out.

175
00:11:32,330 --> 00:11:35,249
We're two heterosexual guys
hanging with the son...

176
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:40,838
...of our other heterosexual friend,
doing the usual straight-guy stuff.

177
00:11:41,089 --> 00:11:43,299
You done?

178
00:11:43,549 --> 00:11:45,051
There's our stop.

179
00:11:45,301 --> 00:11:47,929
Get out of here!
This is our stop.

180
00:11:48,179 --> 00:11:50,098
You guys live around here too?

181
00:11:50,348 --> 00:11:54,686
We live in the building
by the sidewalk.

182
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:57,981
You know it?

183
00:11:58,231 --> 00:12:03,820
Since we're neighbors, what do you say
we get together for a drink?

184
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:10,076
So you want to go to Markel's?

185
00:12:10,326 --> 00:12:12,287
Sure, they love us over there.

186
00:12:12,537 --> 00:12:15,331
Where's your baby?

187
00:12:20,208 --> 00:12:22,544
Ben! Ben!

188
00:12:22,794 --> 00:12:26,256
That's good. Maybe he'll
hear you and pull the cord!

189
00:12:26,506 --> 00:12:29,426
Stop the bus!

190
00:12:36,766 --> 00:12:39,102
Are you sure he didn't break it?
It hurts.

191
00:12:39,352 --> 00:12:43,189
No, it's just a good bone bruise.

192
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:48,069
And right here is
the puncture wound from your ring.

193
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:50,989
- I'm really sorry.
- It's okay.

194
00:12:51,239 --> 00:12:52,782
Sorry.

195
00:12:53,033 --> 00:12:56,953
Sorry! I got my S's back!

196
00:12:57,203 --> 00:13:00,206
Which we can celebrate later.

197
00:13:00,457 --> 00:13:03,418
Celebrate. Celebrate...

198
00:13:03,668 --> 00:13:05,462
<i>He was a double, double</i>

199
00:13:05,712 --> 00:13:10,091
<i>Double-jointed boy</i>

200
00:13:10,342 --> 00:13:14,679
So are you the
professional guitar player?

201
00:13:14,929 --> 00:13:16,848
Yeah, I'm Stephanie.

202
00:13:17,098 --> 00:13:22,437
Right. My name was on there,
but now it just says carrot cake.

203
00:13:23,647 --> 00:13:26,733
So how many chords do you know?

204
00:13:26,983 --> 00:13:30,820
- All of them.
- So you know D?

205
00:13:31,488 --> 00:13:34,157
Do you know A-minor?

206
00:13:35,784 --> 00:13:39,829
Do you know how to go
from D to A-minor?

207
00:13:42,666 --> 00:13:47,003
So does your guitar have a strap?

208
00:13:48,588 --> 00:13:51,216
Mine does.

209
00:13:53,468 --> 00:13:57,180
<i>Stephanie knows all the chords</i>

210
00:13:58,306 --> 00:14:01,601
Come on! Pick up, pick up!

211
00:14:01,768 --> 00:14:03,979
Transit Authority?

212
00:14:04,229 --> 00:14:05,855
I'm doing research for a book.

213
00:14:06,106 --> 00:14:11,778
I was wondering what somebody might do
if they left a baby on a city bus.

214
00:14:12,028 --> 00:14:14,698
Yes, I realize that would be
a stupid character.

215
00:14:14,948 --> 00:14:17,534
Here's the deal:
We lost a car seat on a bus.

216
00:14:17,784 --> 00:14:21,162
It's white plastic and
it fits onto a stroller.

217
00:14:21,413 --> 00:14:24,332
And there was a baby in it.

218
00:14:24,583 --> 00:14:27,377
He wants to talk to you.

219
00:14:27,836 --> 00:14:31,172
Everybody, let's give a warm
Central Perk welcome to...

220
00:14:31,423 --> 00:14:34,217
<i>Terry's a jerk
And he won't let me work</i>

221
00:14:34,467 --> 00:14:37,888
<i>And I hate Central Perk</i>

222
00:14:41,057 --> 00:14:44,978
To Stephanie Schiffer!

223
00:14:48,565 --> 00:14:54,571
I'd like to start with a song I wrote
for the first man I ever loved.

224
00:14:56,448 --> 00:14:57,866
<i>Zachary...</i>

225
00:14:58,116 --> 00:15:02,495
<i>Are all invited to bite me</i>

226
00:15:10,420 --> 00:15:14,341
We're the guys that called
about the baby! Is he here?!

227
00:15:14,591 --> 00:15:17,719
He's here.

228
00:15:18,762 --> 00:15:20,388
I assume one of you is the father.

229
00:15:20,639 --> 00:15:23,558
- That's me.
- I'm him.

230
00:15:24,726 --> 00:15:30,440
Actually, we're both the father.

231
00:15:37,864 --> 00:15:41,826
Oh, Ben! Hey, buddy.

232
00:15:46,748 --> 00:15:50,669
Please tell me you know
which one is our baby.

233
00:15:50,835 --> 00:15:53,755
That one has ducks on his T-shirt
and this one has clowns.

234
00:15:54,005 --> 00:15:56,049
And Ben was definitely wearing ducks.

235
00:15:56,299 --> 00:15:59,469
Or clowns.

236
00:15:59,803 --> 00:16:04,349
That one's Ben! Remember he had
that cute little mole by his mouth!

237
00:16:04,599 --> 00:16:07,853
Hey, Ben! Remember us?

238
00:16:08,103 --> 00:16:11,147
Okay, the mole came off.

239
00:16:11,398 --> 00:16:14,442
What are we gonna do?

240
00:16:14,693 --> 00:16:16,486
We'll flip for it.
Ducks or clowns.

241
00:16:16,736 --> 00:16:18,905
- Flip for the baby?
- You got a better idea?

242
00:16:19,155 --> 00:16:22,284
All right, call it in the air.

243
00:16:22,534 --> 00:16:23,618
Heads.

244
00:16:23,869 --> 00:16:26,621
Heads, it is.

245
00:16:28,123 --> 00:16:31,710
We have to assign heads to something!

246
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:34,880
Right!

247
00:16:36,089 --> 00:16:41,344
Ducks is heads
because ducks have heads.

248
00:16:44,431 --> 00:16:49,269
What kind of scary-ass clowns
came to your birthday?

249
